# Todoist Points — backup configuration (self-hosted home-server box).
#
# Copy this file to `.env.backup` in the repo root and fill in values:
#     cp .env.backup.example .env.backup
#
# The real `.env.backup` is GITIGNORED and must NEVER be committed. Even so,
# there are no secrets here — the rclone Google Drive OAuth token lives only in
# rclone's own config (~/.config/rclone/rclone.conf), never in this file.
#
# Every var has a sane default in scripts/backup.sh; uncomment to override.

# Live SQLite DB on the host (bind-mounted into the container at /data).
# DB_PATH=/home/<user>/todoist-points/data/todoist-points.db

# Where on-box snapshots are written.
# LOCAL_BACKUP_DIR=/home/<user>/todoist-points/data/backups

# Internal state (checksums + last-Drive-push timestamp). Gitignored.
# STATE_DIR=/home/<user>/todoist-points/data/.backup-state

# rclone remote + folder to push snapshots to. The remote ("gdrive") is created
# with `rclone config` (see DEPLOY.md); the folder is auto-created on first copy.
# REQUIRED for the Drive push — if unset, local snapshots still run but the
# Drive push is skipped with a warning (exit 0, so the timer isn't marked failed).
RCLONE_DEST=gdrive:todoist-points-backups

# Retention: keep the newest N snapshots locally and on Drive (the rolling
# "recent" ring buffer). Must be positive integers (>= 1).
# LOCAL_RETENTION=100
# DRIVE_RETENTION=50

# Daily long-tail tier: in addition to the rolling DRIVE_RETENTION snapshots,
# the script keeps at most ONE snapshot per UTC day in a `daily/` subfolder under
# RCLONE_DEST, retained for the newest N days. This defends against unnoticed
# logical corruption that would otherwise rotate out of the fast-moving recent
# ring buffer. Must be a positive integer (>= 1). Default 30 (~a month of days).
DAILY_RETENTION=30

# Minimum minutes between successful Drive pushes (the timer fires more often
# than this; the script throttles the off-box push to this cadence).
# DRIVE_PUSH_INTERVAL_MIN=15
